The Estonian course will give the basic knowledge of the Estonian grammar and vocabulary.
The main topics:
TERE TULEMAST! Welcome!
EESTI JA TARTU. Estonia and Tartu
EESTI KEEL. Estonian language
TEEMA 1. TERE! SAAME TUTTAVAKS! Hello! Let's get acquainted
TEEMA 2. MINA OLEN ... I am ...
TEEMA 3. MINU LEMMIKUD. My favourites
TEEMA 4. POES JA KOHVIKUS. In the shop and in the café
TEEMA 5. MINU PÄEV. My day
TEEMA 6. PERE JA SUGULASED. Family and relatives

The main topics (grammar):
* Cases in singular: basic cases, local cases of singular, comitative and abessive of singular. Nominative plural, genitive Plural
* Personal pronouns, possessive pronouns, adjectives, cardinal numbers;
* Present tense;
* Imperative mood;
* ma- and da-infinitiveObjectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims to teach the basics of Estonian grammar and vocabulary. The intended outcome of the course is level A1.1 ( beginners) in all the language skills.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  On completion of the course the students will be able * to understand and use some Estonian cases, conjugate Estonian verbs in the present, use the imperative and use adjectives and cardinal numbers. * to communicate in easier everyday situations in a shop, at a restaurant or cafe and talk and write about themselves, their family, daily activities and food and drinks and what they like and dislike. * to understand and create elementary-level oral and written texts.
